<br>
&quot;It is a complete as there is nothing to find!&quot;  Tobon spoke sharply.<br>
<br>
I looked around the room.  We were the only ones save for the clockwork librarians.  &quot;You really can't expect for me to believe that my parents were merchants.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The truth is what you should believe.  Your parents were merchants who, regrettably, died and orphaned you at a young age.&quot;<br>
<br>
I stared at him in silence.<br>
<br>
&quot;See, this is why you are not as advanced as you could be.&quot;  He sighed.  &quot;You are always too busy worrying about matters that are unimportant.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;My lineage is not unimportant.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That's not what I meant.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Then what did you mean?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Look, I'm sorry you had to grow up alone without any family, but why this sudden need to find out about them?&quot;<br>
<br>
I looked down at the table before I said a word.  &quot;I have met many these past few months and even joined a guild.&quot;<br>
<br>
As if to a question Tobon said.  &quot;Tinkers Pride.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes.  They...they kind of remind me of the family I never had.  When I originally came to you for any information on my parents you told me they had been merchants and sent me o Larkon who gave me the maps left by them.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I remember.  We felt they would aid you in your journeys.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And they have, but why would a merchant go to Mistmoor or Guk?  Why would there be information on the creatures and notes on their fighting techniques?&quot;<br>
<br>
I had him.  I knew I did but I dared not smile.  Not even a glimmeer or one.  The best thing now was to feel him out.  Wait for the next lie.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot;  he said, &quot;obviously your father had some trade routes through there or at the very least sold the information to would be adventurers.&quot;<br>
<br>
I could tell by the look on him face, in his eyes, that it was a lie.  Standing I leanded over the table and whispered.  &quot;I don't know why or what the Eldrich Collecitive is hiding from me, but  I will find out.  If not by you then by some other means.  How afraid are all of you of what I may stumble upon?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sit down!&quot;  He hissed looking around for eavesdroppers.  &quot;Okay, I will tell you and what I tell you is not to be repeated to anyone.  Understand?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, I understand.&quot;  I said leaning forward.  &quot;I will not tell anyone what you tell me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You have one known relative still alive.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What!  Who?&quot;  I spoke astonished.<br>
<br>
He hesitated.  I could tell he was seriously thinking against telling me.  &quot;You...you have an uncle.  Your father's brother.  His name is Freddie Dooger...&quot;<br>
<br>
