<br>
Feddie Dooger sat beside a fire warming his hands and humming a tune I remembred but could not place.  I know now which side of the family I get my poor musical ability.  He then began to fix his dinner of rat kabobs.<br>
<br>
I didn't know what to say or do so I did what I thought best...being straigtforward.  &quot;I've come for answers.&quot;<br>
<br>
With one swift motion he was on the other side of the campfire dagger in hand.  &quot;Who is there?&quot;  He said.  &quot;Who thinks they are tough?&quot;  Feddie's eyes darted back and forth and then soflty he spoke again almost in a whisper.  &quot;Who speaks on the wind?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't come to fight.  I came to talk.&quot;  I tried to sound brave.  I knew it didn't work.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not fight?&quot;  He chuckled.  &quot;Then you will die.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No, you don't understand.  I...I am told I am your nephew.&quot;<br>
<br>
His face became puzzled as he straightened.  &quot;Jaroo?&quot;<br>
<br>
My heart sank.  I guess until that moment I thought it had been a lie and then I did something potectially stupid. I dropped my invisibility spell.  &quot;Yes, it's me uncle.&quot;<br>
<br>
He crouched were he stood and dropped his dagger.  &quot;Well bless my...&quot;  As he cut himself short he looked away, chuckled, and looked back at me through th fire grinning evilly.  It scared me, but not as much as his next words.  &quot;Hoped this day would come.  Meldrath may take you still.  Don't know...  You hav been killing Minotaurs.  Though not in a while.  I would know.&quot;  Feddie seemed to be talking to himself as he pointed to his eye.  &quot;I have been watching you.  Kept an eye on you I have!  Come and join me by the fire.  Let me get a better look at you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Slowly I advanced and sat across from him.  &quot;What do you mean 'kept an eye on me'?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, yes.  Yes, I have.  Since you were a young one.  A young gnome.  Since they took you away from me.&quot;  His face turned into a scowl.  &quot;Since the Eldritch Collective came and took you away!  They did you know.  Before I got a chance to hand you to Meldrath.  Oh, he was not pleased.  Not pleased at all.<br>
<br>
He had a plan for you.&quot;  Feddie pointed at me, singed his finger in the flames, and stuck it in his mouth.  &quot;Did you know that?  A plan.  Don't know what it was though...&quot;  His voice trailed off, as he seemed to lose himself in thought.<br>
<br>
They idea of being raised by Minotaurs was hard to believe.  What kind of gnome would I have become?  We sat in silence for a while before I spoke.  &quot;What can you tell me of my parents?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Parents?  They are dead.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I know that, but what can you tell me about them?  What were they like?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Are you brave?&quot;  He asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Am...I...well...&quot;  The question surprised me.  &quot;I suppose I am at times though fearful at others.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;My brother, Tovar, was a very brave warrior.  Fierce in battle.&quot;  He chuckled.  &quot;Your mother, well, she was a wizard like yourself.&quot;  He sighed.  &quot;Kae was fearful of her own power.  Too fearful of what might happen.  It became their undoing at the end.  Her fears that is.&quot;<br>
<br>
He grew depressed but I had to know more. &quot;But what happened?  Please, tell me.  I need to know.&quot;<br>
<br>
He put his hands to his head as if to keep his head together.  A single tear ran down his cheek.  &quot;Meldrath sent me and a few others.  Me?  I?  Yes, I and a few others to collect you.  We did too.  Yes, yes, we did take you from them.  From their house by Elizerian Lake.  You did know right?  Oh, no matter really.  It has fallen and destroyed now.   I saw to that.  I could not bear the thought of...&quot;  Another tear rolled down his face.  &quot;Your mother would not cast any spells on whoever held you.  Not even root.  She was afraid you would be harmed.  When I left with you they were supposed to...to...  They were supposed to teleport away.  They should have teleported away.  I found out later that they had fallen.  My poor dear brother.&quot;  He sobbed.  &quot;My poor dear brother died because of my treachery!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And still you do it?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What?&quot;  He stopped crying.  &quot;Of course. They would have died in vain then.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But that makes no sense!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sense?  Of course it makes sense.&quot;  He said drying his eyes.  &quot;It is the Eldritch Collective that killed them.  Meldrath will tell you when you meet him.  They are the true evil ones in Ak'Anon.  It will be restored to its former glory.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Former glory?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why yes.  Surely they have not been able to destroy all evidence.  Look around and you will see.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well there are glowing arcane markings near where King Ak'Anon resides.  I always thought they looked a bit evil.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;King Ak'Anon?&quot;  Feddie spat in disgust.  &quot;A clockwork construct more like!  The Eldritch Collective saw to that and you know what he was?  Well you go find out if I lie to you or not.  You go find out if King Ak'Anon was a ncromancer or not when he was flesh and blood.  If Meldrath is really his brother.  Go!  Get away from me now!  I need my sleep and have done enough talking for tonight.&quot;  Feddie curled up in a ball by the fire.  He looked like a baby in need of his mother.<br>
<br>
As I left I heard him mumble repetitively and stopped to hear him better.  He said.  &quot;Tell m if the madness of Meldrath is real.  Tell me if the madness of Meldrath is real.  Tell me if the madness of Meldrath is real...&quot;<br>
<br>
