<br>
Jaroo looked away clearly troubled.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is it lad?&quot;  Tobon stood from his chair.  &quot;What is wrong?  Did something happen?&quot;<br>
<br>
Slowly shaking his head Jaroo spoke in a barely audible whisper.  &quot;Not yet.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tobo's eyes grew wide.  &quot;What is that suppose to mean?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know what to do...except give up.&quot;  He sat down in an empty chair and looked in his mentor's eyes but found he could not.  &quot;I've tried to be a good wizard.  I've tried to make you proud of me but it seems that I'm jut not...not suited for this life.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nonsense!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Would you stop it!&quot;  Jaroo dropped his staff.  It hit the ground beside him making a loud noise.  &quot;These past few months I've been searching...for something.  I thought it would end when I found out about my family but it didn't.  It only made it worse.  I need a break from everything but it seems that no matter where I go what I do it is all the same.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So what?&quot;  said Tabon.  &quot;You just going to hang up your staff, retire, and live the rest of your days in Ak'Anon?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Then what?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm leaving.  I don't know when I will return.&quot;  Jaroo sighed deeply as if a burden had somehow been lifted.  &quot;I figure I would take some time and try to find who I really am.  Maybe live with the gnomes in Katta and learn their ways for a while.  Maybe...maybe get lost along the way.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And you think that will help?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Honestly, I really don't know at this point.&quot;  Jaroo looked up at him.  His eyes marked with tears.<br>
<br>
Tobon put a hand on the young gnomes shoulder.  &quot;You will be sorely missed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Jaroo was silent.<br>
<br>
&quot;What of your guild?  What of you friends?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;They'll be alright.  I have to believe that.  There is an event that they are holding in a couple of day.  It will be the last time I see them before I go.&quot;  He stood, moved to the door, and stopped.  &quot;I wll never forget them.  I still remember the day I met Karizma at the mills, Sabbik at the bank when he gave me food and drink.  Zapoo fighting bandits in West Karana.  Halt, well, I also met her at the mills.&quot;  He smiled.  &quot;I remember all if not most of them.  Even giving Flippus his first bow over at crushbone.&quot;  Jaroo disappeared thru the doorway.<br>
<br>
Tobon watched as the door shut behind Jaroo.  It was a long while that he stood there stunned before he spoke.  &quot;Farewell my friend.  Safe journey to you.&quot;<br>
<br>
