<br>
A few minutes passed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Jaroo?&quot;  He heard his name and stood.  Karizma, one of his dearest freinds, ran up to him.  &quot;Jaroo, I'm glad I found you before you left.&quot;<br>
<br>
He grinned.  &quot;Wanting to see me off?&quot;<br>
<br>
She bonked him on the head.  &quot;Of course.  Sabbik told me you were taking the long way.  No self-ports just using your feet to get wherever your going.  If you would have told me I would have come here with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
He looked away, smiled, and then looked back at her.  &quot;Well, I thought the party was enough.  I know my leaving is sudden and the party wasn't meant to be a going away thing, but...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But you would have rather have said your goodbyes and leave without it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not at first.&quot;  He said.  &quot;I think I realized just how much I am going to miss all of you.  I almost decided not too.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Then don't.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's not that simple.&quot;  He said shaking his head.  &quot;There are a lot of things to work out.  Things I need some time away to figure out.&quot;<br>
<br>
Karizma sighed.  &quot;I'm not going to tell you I understand your reasons, but I trust you enough to know what you are doing.  I mean.  We practically grew up together.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah,&quot; he smiled.  &quot;Remember that time we deciced to hunt elementals?  It was around the time we met.  One started coming for us when we relized that they can only be hurt by magic.&quot;<br>
<br>
Karizma laughed, &quot;Didn't we run to the guards at the mills because of that?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No, we stayed and won.  We had the help of that enchanter we were friends with at the time.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yeah!&quot;  Remembered Karizma.  &quot;What was her name?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ziskina.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What ever happened to her?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know.&quot;  Jaroo shruged.  &quot;She just disappeared one day.&quot;<br>
<br>
They grew quit.  Karizma saw a pixie trickster fly by.  She stared at it as it disappeared into the forest.  &quot;Won't be long until the spires become active.&quot;  She spoke in an almost distant gloomy voice.<br>
<br>
Jaroo nodded following her gaze.  &quot;I should tell you something.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What i it?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Um,&quot; he chuckled.  &quot;I was over near Ogguk one day and...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Eww, why were you there?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I wrote on the side of their city wall:  Good time.  Mixie.  Gnome.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You didn't!&quot;  She gasped.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes.&quot;  Jaroo laughed.  &quot;Then I went to Grobb and wrote:  For a Trollish good time.  Mixie the Gnome.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Nexue Scion chuckled.<br>
<br>
&quot;You didn't!  Oh, Jaroo, you know what will happen now.&quot;  Karizma laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm hoping they will find her so she won't bother you anymore.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm laughing but if we get over run with Ogres and Troll saying:  Me want good time.  Me want good time. It' going to turn out real bad.&quot;<br>
<br>
Jaroo contemplated.  &quot;Oh...um...I guess I should have thought  of that.&quot;<br>
<br>
They broke out into laughter.<br>
<br>
The Nexus Scion announced that the spires were about to become active.<br>
<br>
&quot;No!&quot; Karizma yelled.  &quot;It's too soon!&quot;<br>
<br>
Jaroo stood and moved to the center of the spires.  &quot;Thank your brother Sabbik for telling you where I was.&quot;  He said as light surrounded him.  &quot;Don't forgt me, Kar.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You know I won't.&quot;  She waved with tears in her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;You've been like a sister to me.  Alot of the Tinks have been like siblings.&quot;  He grinned one last time at her and vanished.<br>
<br>
Running to where he had stood she looked up as the blue spell energy shot up toward Luclin.  &quot;I'll never forget you Jaroo and I will always miss you.&quot;<br>
<br>
