A Final Farewell?<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 Flippus lay on his sleeping bag staring up into the night sky. OtherWorld events had kept him from Jaroo's Farewell party and a hollow feeling began to grow in his gut. &quot;Bert? Do you think he knows that I'll miss him?&quot;<br>
<br>
Bertoxxulous sat a few feet away near the fire. He had assumed the form of a giant plague rat and was toasting a marshmellow over the flames. &quot;I must say Flippus, this emotion of &quot;missing him&quot; is quite unbecoming of a Servant of the Plaguebringer.&quot;<br>
<br>
