<br>
&quot;Escaping?&quot;  Tobon felt the word slip from his mouth.  &quot;But he was gone.  For over a month now.&quot;  He turned.  &quot;I don't...&quot;<br>
<br>
A cry of pain came from the bed.  Jaroo tensed up and shook.<br>
<br>
Digetha ran to him and cast a spell of healing.  &quot;He's been like this every so often.  It gets more infrequent so I think it is passing.&quot;<br>
<br>
Jaroo mumbled.<br>
<br>
&quot;What's he saying?  Manik asked.<br>
<br>
Digetha leaned over him to hear him better.  Hearing one word a cold shiver ran past her.  &quot;He's saying 'Meldrath'.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh dear lord.&quot; breathed Tobon.<br>
<br>
Manik gave a disappointed look at him.  &quot;You should never have told him about his parents.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I doubt that had anything to do with it.&quot; snapped Tobon.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well if you would have at least told hi...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Stop it both of you!&quot;  Digetha yelled cutting Manik off. &quot;He'll be waking soon and hearing an argument will not help.  Go outside if you must.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm awake.&quot;  Jaroo sat up weak, looked over at them, and grinned.  &quot;Heya Tobon.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tobon smiled back.  &quot;How are you feeling?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Weak though I can feel my strength returning.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you remember?  Tell us what happened.&quot;  Manik butted in.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, would you let him have a moments peace?&quot;  Tobon snapped.<br>
<br>
&quot;What&quot; said Manik confused.<br>
<br>
