<br>
His face turned to fright.  &quot;Me...  Why me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why not?  Meldrath put a plan in motion to capture me twice.  Once a baby and once just recently.  The Minotaur's are his allies as are you.  Ya told me yerself that my parents were not ment to die but they did.  I will have my revenge on all of you.  You think you are spared because you are my uncle?  I don't care if you have been driven mad by Meldrath because you know what?  So have I.&quot;  I bashed him with my shield, which knocked him backwards to the ground.  &quot;Now get up and fight!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You... you don't understand!  I could have been your father.&quot; He pleaded cowering.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't lie to me!&quot;   I said swinging my axe toward him.  He dodged and stood with dagger in hand.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can't defeat me nephew.&quot;  Feddie said the fear in his voice clearly gone.<br>
<br>
I laughed at him.  If he didn't know already then he knew now that I have changed.  I was no longer the weak wizard who could barely survive a fight.  I was much more now and I was not about to be tricked by his words.<br>
<br>
We were evenly matched it seemed.  If not for my spell life tap  would'nt have survived, but in the end he fell. I didn't kill him. Maybe I should have but I had another plan.  Garret had been right.  I needed to face my fears and it was time to face another.<br>
<br>
Grabbing Feddie by the shoulder I shook him from unconsciousness.  His eyes slowly opened.  &quot;Now listen carefully 'uncle'.  I have a message that I want you to deliver to Meldrath.  You tell him that I am leaving this area for a while but when the time is right I will be coming for him.  Not today and certainly not tomorrow but soon and when that day comes one of us will die.  Either way or whatever happens I will be at peace o I don't care either way.  You understand this?&quot;<br>
<br>
Feddie slowly nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good, because I would hate to have to come back here and pin a letter saying the same thing to your corpse.&quot;<br>
<br>
I took his dagger and spit on him before leaving.  I felt much better.<br>
